{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480529","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480529"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:45:25+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:45:25+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"64"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/64"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.73,0.1,0.01,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"64"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76424"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/64"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"64"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61921"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"42"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"140"},{"type":"tags","id":"1263"},{"type":"tags","id":"4945"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4988"},{"type":"tags","id":"6233"},{"type":"tags","id":"10741"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11640"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"194"},{"type":"contributions","id":"213"},{"type":"contributions","id":"677"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41976"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76424","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76424"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old man is referred to the Endocrine clinic with two episodes of fractures following minor falls while running. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. He drinks one can of beer per night. He reports breast enlargement since puberty, which was noted during adolescence but not investigated. He works as a software engineer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. His height is 188 cm. He has bilateral gynaecomastia and small, firm testes (volume 4 mL bilaterally) with normal penile size. The remainder of the examination is unremarkable.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cirrhosis","Klinefelter syndrome","Kallmann syndrome","Testicular malignancy","Prolactinoma"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with several classic features of \u003Cstrong\u003EKlinefelter syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E: tall stature, small testes, gynaecomastia, and reduced bone density (evidenced by fragility fractures). Klinefelter syndrome is caused by an additional X chromosome (47,XXY) and is the most common chromosomal disorder in males, affecting 1 in 500-1000 live male births. Many cases remain undiagnosed until adulthood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECirrhosis\u003C/strong\u003E can cause gynaecomastia due to altered hormone metabolism in the liver, but this patient\u0027s modest alcohol intake and absence of other signs of liver disease make this unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKallmann syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by hypogonadotropic hypogonadism and anosmia. Unlike Klinefelter syndrome, these patients typically have short stature and may have associated midline defects such as cleft palate.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETesticular malignancy\u003C/strong\u003E can present with gynaecomastia due to beta-HCG production, but would typically present as a testicular mass rather than small, firm testes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProlactinoma\u003C/strong\u003E can cause gynaecomastia and hypogonadism but typically presents with headaches, visual field defects, and galactorrhoea, none of which are present here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe diagnosis of Klinefelter syndrome is confirmed with karyotype analysis. Management includes testosterone replacement therapy to improve bone density, muscle mass, and quality of life. Regular monitoring of bone density, metabolic parameters, and psychological support are important aspects of ongoing care.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Klinefelter syndrome (47,XXY) is the most common chromosomal disorder in males, affecting 1 in 500-1000 live male births.","Classic features of Klinefelter syndrome include tall stature, small testes, gynaecomastia, and reduced bone density.","Early recognition and testosterone replacement can improve bone density, muscle mass, and quality of life in Klinefelter syndrome."],"references":["Kanakis G, Nieschlag E. Klinefelter syndrome: more than hypogonadism. Metabolism. 2018;86:135-144. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29382506/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61921"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"64"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61921","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61921"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T13:50:59+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T13:50:59+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"64"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76424"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"20